IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Business promotion in the Fox Cities
IRS990.MissionDescription: The mission of the Chamber is to create a positive economic, political and social climate in the Fox Cities, thereby making it possible for members and the community to grow and prosper.
IRS990.Description: Promoted the commercial, industrial and civic interests of the Fox Cities Metropolitan Area with more than 1,400 members.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: PART X - Effective August 1, 2009, the Organization has adopted the guidance for accounting for uncertainty in income taxes which is part of Accounting Standards Codification (ASC) 740-10. This guidance increases the relevancy and comparability of financial reporting by clarifying the way organizations account for uncertainties in income tax positions taken or expected to be taken. It makes recognition and measurement more consistent as well as offering clear criteria for subsequently recognizing, derecognizing and measuring such tax positions for financial statement purposes. This adoption had no impact on the Organization's consolidated financial position, results of activities or cash flows.

Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Identifier: Procedure for Monitoring Grants in the U.S.:
Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: Schedule I, Part I, Line 2: A grant committee reviews and approves each grant application based on the following requirements. (1) The request comes from a not-for-profit organization. (2) The project improves the quality of downtown Appleton or the surrounding Fox Cities communities, and enhances our quality of life. (3) The project showcases a downtown area, improves our community's image and/or strengthens the Fox Cities economy. (4) The project benefits people throughout the Fox Cities.

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: The Chamber pays for social club dues for the president. The portion of membership for personal use is treated as a taxable compensation to the president. The club membership is used to promote Chamber membership and enhance Chamber membership relationships.

The Chamber does not have a written policy for paying club membership, but follows their established standard procedures. The Chamber pays for the cost of monthly club membership. Individual employees are responsible for covering the minimum meals charge if it goes unused. The Chamber will reimburse employees for all business related expenses tied to the membership. Employees will cover personal expenses at the club. Employees will cover any special assessments levied by the club. Employees will estimate the percentage of their club membership utilized for personal use, so the benefit can be reported as an employee taxable benefit.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 6
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Chamber is organized as a non-stock, non-profit corporation with members. Each membership account shall be entitled to cast one membership vote at any regular or special meeting of the organization.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE Board of Directors is provided a copy of the Form 990, and the President reviews the Form 990 before signing and filing the Form 990.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Organization has recently adopted a new conflict of interest policy. The Organization intends to have their Board of Directors review the conflict of interest policy annually, and annually sign a conflict of interest statement.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A committee comprised of the current chair, past chair, and chair elect evaluates the President. The Committee examines compensation data from similar organizations and obtains input from the board and others. Then, the committee submits a recommendation to the executive committee for approval. The organization does not have other officers that receive compensation.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CHAMBER MAKES COPIES OF ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO ITS MEMBERS UPON REQUEST.
